(1, '8e4470ad-9efb-4cf1-9fb3-44e9aa0d58e6', 'GB', '2 Years', 'Scale-up Visa United Kingdom', 'workvisa', 1, 1, 1, 0, '<h2>The Scale-up visa is a new immigration method that will become available on August 22, 2022. It is intended for eligible UK firms with the potential for expansion and will make it easier for them to hire qualified&nbsp;<a href=\"https://stats.oecd.org/glossary/detail.asp?ID=1047\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 123, 255);\">foreign workers</a>.</h2><h2>A new points-based pathway for migrant workers hired by a UK scale-up sponsor is termed a scale-up visa. It is intended for those who possess the expertise required to support the sponsor\'s firm as it expands. With this visa, persons who have a legitimate employment offer at the necessary skill level from the reputable UK scale-up business can be approved for a fast-track visa.</h2>', '<h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\">You are eligible for this visa if you;</h2><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\">have been given a job offer that has been confirmed to work for a scale-up company for at least six months.</h2><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\">your employer has provided you with a \"certificate of sponsorship\" that includes details on the position that has been offered to you in the UK.</h2><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\">have been offered a job in one of the categories of eligible employment.</h2>', '<h2>While applying for this visa, you must provide;</h2><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\">Your reference number that your employer provided you with your sponsorship certificate.</h2><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\">Evidence of your English knowledge and proficiency.</h2><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\">A passport or proof of identity and nationality.</h2><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\">Your name, position, and yearly salary.</h2><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\">The occupation code for your work.</h2><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\">The identity of your company and their sponsor licence number, as stated on your sponsorship certificate.</h2>', '<h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"color: gray;\">When to Apply</strong></h2><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\">You may apply for this visa up to three months prior to the day you are scheduled to begin employment in the UK. Your sponsorship certificate includes this date. You must present identification documentation and supporting documents as part of your application.</h2><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Visa Processing Time</strong></h2><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\">The visa processing time depends on the time needed to process your documents. This visa is usually processed in three to eight weeks. It can take longer depending on various factors. So, you shall be prepared for any kind of delays.</h2><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"color: gray;\">How to Apply</strong></h2><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\">The detailed process of application varies depending on whether you are applying from inside or outside of the country. However, the basic steps are the same. You are required to contact the embassy, provide the necessary documents and pay the visa fee.</h2>', '<h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Duration</strong></h2><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\">Scale-up employees will receive authorization that is good for two years. The sponsorship will initially terminate after six months, at which point they are free to look for work elsewhere without having an impact on the conditions of their visa. After the first six months, applicants have the option to continue working there or start their own business.</h2><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Fees</strong></h2><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\">The scale-up visa will cost you 715 GBP. The same amount of fee is required for each dependent applying with you.</h2>', '<h2><span style=\"color: rgb(48, 48, 48);\">As long as you are considered eligible, you may extend your visa an unlimited number of times for a period of three years. You might be eligible to seek permanent residence in the UK after five years.</span></h2>', '<h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Business</strong></h2><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\">You can be self-employed after working with an employer for six months.</h2><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Travel</strong></h2><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\">You are allowed to travel throughout the country.</h2><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Extension</strong></h2><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\">This visa is extendable and can even lead to permanent residence.</h2><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Dependents</strong></h2><h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\">Include family members, if any.</h2>', NULL, 'vite___react___ts1725697022428-6792.jpeg', '', 1, '2024-09-07 08:17:02', '2024-09-08 05:10:27', NULL),
(2, '5956a4b7-2fb3-40b2-a322-03341df98eb0', 'GB', '3 years', 'Innovator Visa UK', 'workvisa', 1, 1, 1, 0, '<h2 class=\"ql-align-justify\">Apply for an Innovator Visa if:</h2><ul><li>Suppose you want to start and operate an innovative business in the UK. In that case, your product or service must be unique compared to currently available.</li><li>An authorised body, often known as an endorsing body, has endorsed your company or business idea.</li></ul><p><br></p>', '<p>You are eligible for an Innovator Visa if you fulfil the following conditions.</p><ul><li>Suppose you want to launch and operate an innovative business in the UK. In that case, your product or service must be unique compared to other offerings.&nbsp;</li><li>An authorised body, also known as an endorsing body, has supported your company or business proposal.</li></ul><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">If you want to launch a new company</strong></p><p>Suppose you wish to start a new firm. In that case, you must have a minimum&nbsp;of £50,000 in investment money before applying for an Innovator Visa. You\'ll have to provide evidence of your financing source.</p><p>You don\'t require any investment funds if:</p><ul><li>your company is already founded and has received a previous visa endorsement, or</li><li>you\'ve previously informed your endorsing body of the change in your business.</li></ul><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Supporting yourself</strong></p><p>For the previous 28 days, you had to have at least £1,270 in your bank account before you either:</p><ul><li>Apply for Innovator Visa</li><li>Suppose you have been in the United Kingdom for less than a year. In that case, you can seek to convert to an Innovator Visa or renew your Innovator Visa.</li></ul><p>You cannot rely on one or both of the following to sustain yourself:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>The proceeds of your investment portfolio&nbsp;</li><li>Money made from illegally working in the UK</li></ul><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Sharing of Investment funds</strong></p><p>Together with other Innovator applicants, you cannot share the very same investment capital, but you may join a team. For each Innovator applicant, your team needs £50,000. For instance, if your team has two Innovator applicants, it needs £100,000 to invest.</p>', '<p class=\"ql-align-justify\">You must provide an \"<a href=\"https://lettersamples.net/l/endorsement-letter-definition-types-and-format-of-writing\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 123, 255);\">endorsement letter</a>\" with your application to demonstrate that an endorsing body has reviewed your firm or business plan. You are also required to provide the following.</p><ul><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">A current passport or other proof of identity and nationality.</li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">Bank statements demonstrate that you have at least £1,270 in savings for at least 28 days before applying.</li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">Evidence that you can communicate in English.&nbsp;</li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">Proof of your investment cash is required if you are starting a new firm.&nbsp;</li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">If you are from a nation where you must take the test, the results of your tuberculosis test.</li></ul><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">You must provide translated documents by a certified translator if these aren\'t in Welsh or English.</p><p><br></p>', '<p>You must provide identification documentation as part of your application. Depending on your country of origin and passport type, there are many ways to accomplish this.</p><p>You\'ll either:</p><ul><li>Get a biometric residency permit by taking your fingerprints and photo at a visa application centre.&nbsp;</li><li>You can create or sign in to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/using-your-uk-visas-and-immigration-account#your-ukvi-account\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 123, 255);\">your UK Visas and Immigration (UKVI) account</a>&nbsp;while scanning your identity document using the \"UK Immigration: ID Check\" app.</li></ul><p>When you apply, you\'ll be instructed what to do.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">When to Apply</strong></p><p>You can apply as early as three months before your desired departure date.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Visa Processing Time</strong></p><p>Once you\'ve submitted an online application, verified your identification, and presented your papers, a decision on your visa is often made within:</p><ul><li>3 weeks - if you\'re outside the UK</li><li>8 weeks - if you\'re inside the UK</li></ul><p><br></p>', '<p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Duration</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">If either of the following applies, you may remain for three years.</p><ul><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">If you come to the UK on an Innovator Visa.</li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">In case of switching to this visa from another visa while in the UK.</li></ul><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">You can request to extend your stay for three years when your visa expires. You can extend this visa many times.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Fees</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">Whether you apply for yourself or your partner and child (if any), the cost is £1,021 for each person if you apply from outside the UK.&nbsp;</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">If you are extending or switching while in the UK, the cost is £1,277 for each person.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p>', '<p class=\"ql-align-justify\">If both of the following are true, you may apply to renew your Innovator Visa.</p><ul><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">You comply with the eligibility&nbsp;requirements.</li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">You want to start a new company or are still operating in the UK.</li></ul><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">If you want to extend the visa of your spouse or kids, you must apply separately. They can apply either at the same time as you or whenever their existing visa expires.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">To start a new firm, you need £50,000 in investment capital. There is no need for funds if either of the following applies to you.</p><ul><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">Your company is already founded and has received a previous visa endorsement, or</li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\">You\'ve altered your business and have already agreed with your endorsing body about it.</li></ul><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">When you extend your visa, you must have an approving body evaluate your company or business concept.</p><p><br></p>', '<p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Business</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">You can establish one or more enterprises and work for them, including serving as a director while employed or as a self-employed partner in a commercial partnership.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Dependants</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">If your partner and kids qualify as your \"dependants,\" you may bring them.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Multi-entry</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">You can leave the country and come back to the UK.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Residence&nbsp;</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">Suppose you\'ve been in the UK for three years and are otherwise eligible. In that case, you can apply to settle here&nbsp;permanently (sometimes known as \"<a href=\"https://visalobby.com/visa-and-immigration/indefinite-leave-to-remain-uk\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 123, 255);\">indefinite permission to remain</a>\").</p><p><br></p>', NULL, 'pexels-donaldtong94-1893331725697889442-4823.jpg', '', 1, '2024-09-07 08:31:29', '2024-09-08 05:10:27', NULL),
(3, '24f7b338-1b70-4420-8352-d86a1697838d', 'GB', '1 - 5 Years', 'Skilled Worker Visa UK', 'workvisa', 1, 0, 1, 0, '<p>A Skilled Worker Visa lets you enter or remain in the UK to work for an approved employer in an eligible job. This visa replaced the Tier 2 (General) Work Visa.</p>', '<p>To be eligible, you need to meet the following requirements:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Work for a home office-approved employer in the UK.</li><li>Get from the employer a \'certificate of sponsorship\'. It should provide detail about the position offered to you in the UK.</li><li>Do employment which is on the list of the&nbsp;eligible occupation.&nbsp;</li><li>You will be paid a minimum wage based on your job type.</li></ul><p>The specific eligibility depends on your job. You need a job offer before applying for your visa.</p><p>You need to be able to read, speak, write and understand English. You may need to prove your English. Suppose you are not eligible for this visa. In that case, you may qualify for any other type of UK work visa.</p>', '<p>You need to provide the following documents.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>A valid passport or other document proving your identity and nationality.</li><li>A certificate of sponsorship reference number - your employer will provide you with this proof of your knowledge of English.</li><li>Your title and yearly salary.</li><li>The occupation code for your job.</li><li>Your employer\'s name and sponsor licence number - will appear on your sponsorship certificate.</li></ul><p>If you received your certificate of sponsorship before December 1, 2020, it would need to be updated because it was issued before the Tier 2 (General) Work Visa was changed by the Skilled Worker Visa. In the UK, visa sponsorship management system request that your employer update the \'sponsor notes\' section.</p><p>Depending on your circumstances, you might also need other documents.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Financial&nbsp;</strong></p><p>Bank statements, for example, can demonstrate that you have sufficient personal savings to support yourself in the UK. Unless your certificate of sponsorship shows that your employer can&nbsp;support you.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Criminal Records</strong></p><p>You give a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.workplacetesting.com/definition/710/criminal-record-check\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 123, 255);\">&nbsp;criminal record&nbsp;</a>certificate if you are applying from outside the UK and you work in:</p><ul><li>Healthcare&nbsp;includes doctors, nurses, paramedics, dentists, managers, ophthalmic opticians, pharmacists, and dental nurses.&nbsp;</li><li>Education&nbsp;includes school inspectors, teachers, childminders, education advisers, and teaching assistants.&nbsp;</li><li>Therapy, such as speech and language therapists, psychologists, and counsellors.</li><li>Social services, such as social workers and managers.</li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Inform if you have lived in more than one country</strong></p><p>You may require to provide a certificate from each country depending on your age and duration of stay.</p><p>Other documents that you could be asked for include:</p><ul><li>Proof your relationship with your children or partner if they apply.</li><li>Result of tuberculosis test if you are from one of the listed countries.</li><li>Your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ukuni.net/articles/what-atas-certificate\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 123, 255);\">ATAS certificate</a>&nbsp;must be valid if your job requires you need it. Your job role is about researching a sensitive subject at a PhD or higher level.&nbsp;</li><li>Your UK PhD certificate or unique&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.lawinsider.com/dictionary/ecctis\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 123, 255);\">&nbsp;Ecctis&nbsp;</a>reference number (formerly as unique UK NARIC reference number) if you have a qualification from somewhere other than the UK, you must apply through Ecctis.</li></ul>', '<p>Apply for the Skilled Worker Visa online. Further, you need to prove your identity as part of your application. It is determined by where you are from and the type of passport. When you apply, you\'ll be told what you need to do.&nbsp;</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">When to Apply</strong></p><p>You may apply for a visa three months before your start date in the UK. This start date is printed on the sponsorship certificate which you receive.&nbsp;</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Visa Processing Time</strong></p><p>After you\'ve applied online, verified your identity, and submitted your documents, you should receive a decision on your visa within:</p><ul><li>Suppose you are outside of the UK; it will take 3 weeks.</li><li>It takes 8 weeks if you are inside the UK.</li></ul><p>You may get a faster decision after paying for it. Further, how you do this depends if you are inside or outside the UK.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">How to Apply</strong></p><p>How do you apply depends on whether you are:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>outside of the UK and intend to visit the UK.</li><li>inside the UK and prolonging your current visa.</li><li>or outside of the UK and switch from another visa.</li></ul>', '<p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Duration</strong></p><p>This visa can be valid for five years before it needs to be extended. When this visa expires or if you switch jobs or employers, you must apply to extend or update it.&nbsp;</p><p>You may be eligible to apply after five years for permanent residence in the UK. It is also known as \'indefinite leave to remain. Thus, it gives you the right to live, study and work in the country as much as you want. Also, you can apply for benefits if you qualify.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Fees</strong></p><p>When applying for a Skilled Worker visa, you must have enough money to:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>pay the application fee - depending on your circumstances. The standard fee ranges from £610 to £1,408.&nbsp;</li><li>pay the healthcare surcharge (normally £624 per year)&nbsp;</li><li>you\'ll need at least £1,270 to support yourself once you show up in the UK (unless you\'re exempt).&nbsp;</li></ul><p>There will be a low application fee if your job is on the list of shortage occupations. When applying, they tell you how much you need to pay.</p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Fee when you are outside the UK</strong></p><p>At the time of applying, if you are outside the UK, then the standard fee is determined by how long you will be in the UK. In this case, the standard fee will be as follows.</p><ul><li>Till 3 years -&nbsp;&nbsp;Fee: £610 per person</li><li>For more than 3 years -&nbsp;Fee: £1,220 per person</li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Fee when you are outside the UK</strong></p><p>In case you are inside the UK at the time of applying to switch, extend or update your visa, then the standard fee will depend on whether you will be in the UK for:</p><ul><li>Till 3 years -&nbsp;Fee: £704 per person</li><li>More than 3 years -&nbsp;Fee: £1,408 per person</li></ul>', '<p>If all of the following conditions are met, you can generally apply for&nbsp;extending&nbsp;a Skilled Worker Visa or Tier 2 (General) Work Visa:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>You have the same job as you did when you were granted previous permission to enter or remain in the UK.&nbsp;</li><li>Your occupation is the same as when you were granted previous permission to enter or stay in the UK.&nbsp;</li><li>The company that issued your current sponsorship certificate, you are still employed by them.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>To extend their visa, your partner or children must apply separately. They can apply at the very same time as you or whenever their current visa expires.</p>', '<p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Multi-entry</strong></p><p>You can travel abroad and return to the UK.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Study</strong></p><p>With a skilled worker visa, you are allowed to study.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Work</strong></p><p>You can do the extra paid job&nbsp;on this visa as long as you\'re willing to continue&nbsp;the job for which you are being sponsored. You can also perform unpaid volunteer work.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Extension</strong></p><p>As long you meet the eligibility requirements, you can keep on extending your visa.&nbsp;</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Dependants</strong></p><p>You can bring your partner and children with you as your \'dependants\' if they\'re eligible.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Residence</strong></p><p>You can apply to settle permanently in the UK (also known as \'indefinite leave to remain\') if you have lived in the UK for five years and meet the other eligibility requirements.</p>', NULL, 'pexels-josh-willink-11499-7010161725700092615-1916.jpg', '[\"Work Permit\",\"Stay\",\"Add One\",\"SAdasd\"]', 1, '2024-09-07 09:08:12', '2024-09-08 05:10:27', NULL),
(4, '105d4281-74d2-47cc-abc4-df40dff21f3d', 'AU', 'indefinite', 'Global Talent Visa (Subclass 858) Australia', 'workvisa', 1, 0, 1, 0, '<p>Global Talent Visa (Subclass 858) is for those who have attained an internationally recognised record of outstanding and exceptional achievement in an eligible field. It is a permanent visa. Also, you can work and study in Australia and even sponsor your relatives to come to this country.</p><p>It can be further distinguished into two streamlines:</p><ul><li>The streamlined&nbsp;<strong>Global Talent pathway</strong>&nbsp;is for highly skilled applicants who have attained an internationally recognised record of outstanding and exceptional achievements within the priority sectors. These sectors may include health, resources, digitech, energy, etc.</li><li>The&nbsp;<strong>Distinguished Talent pathway</strong>&nbsp;is for highly talented applicants with an internationally recognised record of exceptional and outstanding achievements working in other sectors for either a profession, sport, arts, or academia and research.</li></ul><p><br></p>', '<p>To be eligible, you must:</p><ul><li>be residing in or outside Australia but not in immigration clearance when you apply and when they grant this visa.</li><li>have international recognition of exceptional achievement in sports, art or academics.</li><li>have an Australian nominator with a national reputation in your area of talent.</li></ul><p><br></p>', '<p>You will need to include documents to support the claims you make in your application and show you meet the visa criteria. It provides evidence of your achievements in an eligible field. Apart from that, the documents needed are given as follows:</p><ul><li>Identity documents such as your photo, personal details, passport issue and expiry dates.</li><li>Evidence of your achievements.</li><li>Provide proof of sufficient funds and that you can work in your field of achievement.</li><li>Prove you have at least&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.netlanguages.com/blog/index.php/2017/08/28/what-is-functional-language/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 123, 255);\">functional English</a>.</li><li>Partner and other dependent\'s documents, if any.</li></ul><p><br></p>', '<p>You must be either inside or outside of Australia at the time of application for this visa. But you should not be in the immigration clearance.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">When to Apply</strong></p><p>The visa may even take months to process. So, at least apply a month before you want to move.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Visa Processing Time</strong></p><p>The Global Talent Pathway visa is processed in 1-3 months. On the other hand, the Distinguished Talent pathway visa takes up to 8 months or more than a year.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">How to Apply</strong></p><p>You may apply in a few steps: Create ImmiAccount, apply online and pay the fee. But the process of application can be complex, so you better let a visa consultant handle it for you.</p>', '<p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Duration</strong></p><p>With Global Talent Visa (Subclass 858), you can stay in Australia permanently, enrol in Australia\'s public health care scheme and travel in and outside Australia for five years. You may also apply for citizenship if eligible.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Fees</strong></p><p>The visa costs AUD 4,180 for the main applicant. There is an extra charge for each family member who applies for the permit with you.</p>', '<p>There is no need for extension of this visa as it is permanent. But you may have to extend your travel permit, which expires after five years.</p>', '<p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Work</strong></p><p>You must be able to work in the field of your expertise.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Multi-entry</strong></p><p>Travel in and outside Australia for five years.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Dependents</strong></p><p>Include family with yourself.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Citizenship</strong></p><p>Apply for citizenship if eligible.</p>', NULL, 'pexels-lara-jameson-88283221725771660371-3036.jpg', '[\"Work\",\"Extendable\",\"Dependants\",\"Citizenship\"]', 1, '2024-09-08 05:01:00', '2024-09-08 05:10:27', NULL),
(5, 'a5692425-9442-4c11-aba7-555395a30ff9', 'AU', '12 months', 'Visitor Visa (SubClass 600) Australia', 'workvisa', 1, 0, 1, 0, '<p>For brief tourism or business stays, nationals of the ETA-eligible or 45 eVisitor countries can apply for a Visitor Visa (SC600) in Australia. Subclass 600 includes many visitor visa categories based on the purpose of the visit and the applicant\'s nationality. The Australia Visitor Visa is valid for three, six, or twelve months. It can be used for single or multiple entries.</p><p>Depending upon the purpose of the visit, there are six streams of Visitor (Subclass 600) Visas;</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Tourist Stream</strong>&nbsp;<strong style=\"color: gray;\">- When applying in Australia</strong></p><p>Using this visa category, you can visit as a tourist, to visit family and friends, or for business or medical treatment.&nbsp;</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Tourist Stream - When applying outside Australia</strong></p><p>This visa category lets you visit Australia as a tourist, on a cruise, or visit family and friends.&nbsp;</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Sponsored Family Stream</strong></p><p>This visa stream allows people who are sponsored, generally by a family member, to visit their family members in Australia.&nbsp;</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Business Visitor Stream</strong></p><p>It allows you to visit for business purposes.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Approved Destination Status Stream</strong></p><p>This visa stream is for citizens from some regions of China visiting Australia on tour organised by an approved travel agent.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Frequent Traveller Stream</strong></p><p>This visa category is for residents of China who frequently travel to Australia for business or pleasure.</p>', '<p>To be eligible;</p><ul><li>You should be a genuine visitor.</li><li>Enough funds for stay and whenever you want to leave.</li></ul><p><br></p>', '<p>You need to include as much information as possible to support your application. It includes English translations of your documents. These documents should be scanned in colour. Thus making them more transparent and legible. The necessary documents may include:</p><ul><li>Passport</li><li>Your recent picture with a white background.</li><li>The Visitor Visa (Subclass 600) form.</li><li><a href=\"https://www.virginiapremier.com/what-is-health-insurance-and-why-is-it-important/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 123, 255);\">Health Insurance</a>&nbsp;proof.</li><li>Letter from a school, employer or a family member settled in Australia.</li><li>Proof of accommodation.</li></ul><p><br></p>', '<p>You need to send all the required documents to apply for the visa. They will inform you if there is a need for biometric verification. If you didn\'t have health exams before applying for the visa, have them if we tell you to.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">When to Apply</strong></p><p>You may apply at least 15 to 30 days before travelling.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Visa Processing Time</strong></p><p>Depending on your nationality and documents, it may take a few days or weeks.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">How to Apply&nbsp;</strong></p><p>The application process is online, and you also have to fill out the form and submit it to the Australian Immigration Office. Always seek professional advice before applying.</p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', '<p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Duration</strong></p><p>It is a short-term visa. It allows you a stay of 3, 6, or even 12 months. You can stay for the duration or dates stated on the visa grant letter.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Fees</strong></p><p>The visa costs AUD 145 for each applicant. You might also have to pay other costs for health checks, police certificates and biometrics.</p><ul><li>Tourist stream (Apply Outside Australia) - Fee: 365 AUD</li><li>Sponsored Family stream - Fee:&nbsp;145 AUD&nbsp;</li><li>Business Visitor stream - Fee: 145 AUD&nbsp;</li><li>Approved Destination Status stream - Fee:&nbsp;145 AUD&nbsp;</li><li>Tourist stream (Apply in Australia) - Fee:&nbsp;370 AUD&nbsp;</li><li>Frequent Traveller stream - Fee:&nbsp;1085 AUD&nbsp;</li></ul><p><br></p>', '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(48, 48, 48);\">You can\'t stay in Australia longer by extending this visa. You must apply for another visa.</span></p>', '<p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Tourism</strong></p><p>Explore the country through a 3-month visa</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Extension</strong></p><p>There is no option for an extension of this visa.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Citizenship</strong></p><p>It<strong style=\"color: gray;\">&nbsp;</strong>is not offered through this visa.</p>', NULL, 'pexels-lara-jameson-88283131725771753408-4776.jpg', '[\"Tourism\",\"Family-Visit\",\"Meetings\"]', 1, '2024-09-08 05:02:33', '2024-09-08 05:10:27', NULL),
(6, '2370195e-437b-4569-9786-f3097b9c9279', 'AU', '3 - 5 Years', 'Student Visa (Subclass 500) Australia', 'studentvisa', 1, 0, 1, 0, '<p>Students enrolled in any course under CRICOS in Australia can apply for the Student Visa (Subclass 500). The visa permits international students to stay in Australia for up to 5 years, but not longer than the duration of their study. So you can stay in Australia for the period of the course.</p><p>The Student Visa (Sub 500) can be used to study any full-time course eligible under Australian visa criteria. Also, international students may apply for it to pursue any full-time degree they want.</p><h3>What can you do with a Student Visa (Subclass 500) in Australia?</h3><ul><li>You can apply online from within or outside of Australia.</li><li>Work up to 40 hours every two weeks once your course begins.</li><li>Participate in the course of study that is eligible.</li><li>Include your family members (your partner or you and your partner\'s dependent child) in your application.</li></ul><p><br></p>', '<p>To be eligible, you must:</p><ul><li>You must be 6 years or older.</li><li>Get enrolled in a course for study in Australia.</li><li>Hold \"Overseas Student Health Cover (OSHC)\" or fall in one of the exemption categories</li><li>Prove you have a welfare arrangement if you are under 18.</li></ul><p><br></p>', '<p>Apart from the primary documents like passport, recently taken a photograph, and visa application form, you need to fulfil specific requirements.</p><ul><li><strong>Age</strong>&nbsp;- More than 6 years of age.</li><li><a href=\"https://www.mylawquestions.com/what-is-parental-consent.htm\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 123, 255);\"><strong>Parental Consent</strong></a><strong>&nbsp;</strong>- Needed for students less than 18 years.</li><li><strong>Academic</strong>&nbsp;- Evidence of previous education (if applicable).</li><li><strong>Financial&nbsp;</strong>- Provide proof that you are financially stable.</li><li><strong>Language&nbsp;</strong>- English language is a must.</li></ul><p><br></p>', '<p>The application process is online, after which you need to make the payment or else the application will not proceed.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">When to Apply</strong></p><p>You must apply 30-45 days before travel.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Visa Processing Time</strong></p><p>The application process may take approximately 30 to 45 days after paying the fee.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">How to Apply</strong></p><p>Create ImmiAccount to apply, gather required documents and pay for the visa. Consult a visa expert before applying.</p>', '<p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Duration</strong></p><p>It is a temporary visa to study for up to 5 years. The type of course and its length will determine the duration of stay. Primary school children enrolled in years 1-4 will generally only be granted a Student Visa for a maximum of 3 years.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Fees</strong></p><p>Unless they are exempt, the primary applicant\'s visa costs 630 AUD. Besides this, every family member applying for a visa must also pay a fee.</p>', '<p>To continue studying in Australia, you must apply for a new Student Visa. In case if your student visa expires before your graduation you might be eligible for a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://visalobby.com/visa-and-immigration/visitor-visa-subclass-600-australia\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 123, 255);\">Visitor Visa (Subclass 600).</a></p><p>After completeing your education, depending upon how long you have been in the country legally, You may be eligible for one of the Work Visa or residence catagories.</p>', '<p>The bearer of this visa recieve various benefits. For example, this visa allows family members to accompany the student, and the student may apply for it.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Multi-Entry</strong></p><p>There is no restriction to multi-entry during the visa.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Work</strong></p><p>Work along with studies.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Dependents</strong></p><p>Family can also accompany you during the stay.</p>', NULL, 'pexels-lara-jameson-88283951725771830553-2402.jpg', '[\"Study\",\"Dependants\"]', 1, '2024-09-08 05:03:50', '2024-09-08 05:10:35', NULL),
(7, '4ca9f9e3-6021-430b-9c60-508243271c4c', 'CA', 'Indefinite', 'Family Sponsorship Canada', 'familyvisa', 1, 0, 1, 0, '<p>A Canadian resident may be able to sponsor certain relatives to immigrate to Canada under the Family Class. But the sponsor needs to be at least 18 years old and a Canadian citizen. A person registered in Canada as an Indian under the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/background-the-indian-act-1.1056988\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 123, 255);\">Canadian Indian Act</a>&nbsp;or a permanent resident of Canada can also sponsor relatives.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">What are your responsibilities as a sponsor?</strong></p><p>A sponsor must sign an agreement promising to provide financial support for your spouse or partner\'s basic needs as well as their dependent children.</p><p><br></p>', '<p>There is an eligibility criteria for both the person who sponsors and the one being sponsored. As for the one sponsoring, they must be:</p><ul><li>Canadian citizen</li><li>A person registered in Canada as an Indian under the Canadian Indian Act or permanent resident of Canada.</li><li>Sponsoring their spouse</li></ul><p>Canadian citizens can sponsor family members only if they meet all of these conditions:</p><ul><li>They’re related by blood or adoption.</li><li>Both their mother and father passed away.</li><li>They’re under 18 years of age.</li><li>They’re single (not married or in a common-law or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www23.statcan.gc.ca/imdb/p3Var.pl?Function=DECI&amp;Id=252425\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 123, 255);\">conjugal relationship</a>).</li></ul><h3>Who qualifies as a family member?</h3><p>Father, mother, father-in-law, mother-in-law, spouse, child, son-in-law, and daughter-in-law are family members. A family member is an individual related to you by blood, adoption or marriage and lives in your home.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Other than the basic document, you need to provide the following documents as well while you apply for family sponsorship:</p><ul><li>Identity documents from both sides</li><li>Sponsorship agreement and undertaking between both parties</li><li>The sponsor must demonstrate that they can support the new family member.</li><li>Documents for additional documents, if any.</li></ul><p><br></p>', '<p>There are two stages to becoming a permanent resident for your eligible relatives. You must apply to sponsor your relatives, and they must apply for permanent residence. You must submit both your sponsorship application and your relative\'s permanent residence application at the same time.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">When to Apply</strong></p><p>The time by which you need to apply varies for countries. You should look for visa processing time for the country you are sponsoring a relative from and apply accordingly.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Visa Processing Time</strong></p><p>Visa processing time may vary according to the country you are applying from. But typically, sponsorship applications take approximately a year to process, but this can take much longer depending on your case type.&nbsp;</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">How to Apply</strong></p><p>The application process is online. Both the parties have to apply simultaneously and provide the necessary documents.</p>', '<p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Duration</strong></p><p>Family sponsorship leads to permanent residence.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Fees</strong></p><p>The sponsorship costs differently according to the age of the person being sponsored. For a child applicant, the application fee is CAD 150. But for an adult (22 or older), this cost goes to CAD 1050.</p>', '<p>The sponsorship leads to permanent residence. Thus, there is not much need to extend your stay in Canada.</p>', '<p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Work</strong></p><p>The sponsored members can work in their field of interest.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Study</strong></p><p>You may continue your studies after getting to Canada.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Tourism</strong></p><p>You may travel in or out of Canada.</p>', NULL, 'pexels-lara-jameson-88283981725772380720-9358.jpg', '[\"Work\",\"Extendable\",\"Dependants\",\"Citizenship\"]', 1, '2024-09-08 05:13:00', '2024-09-08 05:13:00', NULL),
(8, '13039fca-4195-494a-ad74-fd3d52e33c5f', 'CA', 'Indefinite', 'Start-up Visa Program Canada', 'businessvisa', 1, 0, 1, 0, '<h3>Start-up Visa Program in Canada seeks immigrant entrepreneurs with business skills and potential. The opportunity is offered to innovative people who can create jobs for Canadians or can compete on a global scale.</h3><h3><br></h3><h3>The Start-up Visa allows foreign entrepreneurs to set up a shop in Canada and gain permanent residency. If you have business skills and meet some other Start-up Visa requirements, it is a far easier and more secure way to obtain PR (Permanent Residence).</h3><p><br></p><h2>How do I get an endorsement for my Start-Up Visa?</h2><p><br></p><h3>The applicant has a genuine, unique business plan that addresses new or existing market needs or establishes a competitive advantage. The applicant possesses or is actively developing the essential skills, knowledge, experience, and market awareness to run the business successfully.</h3><p><br></p><h2>How can I obtain assistance from a designated organisation?&nbsp;</h2><p><br></p><h3>Firstly, contact the designated organisation to learn how to obtain its assistance. Then you must persuade the organisation that you have a viable business idea worth supporting. Each organisation has its process for pitching its idea. And they have their own requirements. They may ask you to present a business concept in person or to submit a detailed business plan.</h3><p><br></p><h3><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Letter of support</strong></h3><h3>A letter of support will be sent to you if you agree with a designated organisation. Once you submit your application, please include this letter.</h3><p><br></p><h3><strong style=\"color: gray;\">What does this letter say?</strong></h3><h3>This letter acts as evidence that the angel investor group,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://learn.angellist.com/articles/venture-capital-fund\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 123, 255);\">venture capital fund</a>, or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://efinancemanagement.com/financial-management/business-incubation\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 123, 255);\">business incubator</a>&nbsp;believes in your business idea.&nbsp;</h3>', '<h2>To be eligible for the Start-up Visa Program, you need to:</h2><ul><li>receive a \"letter of support\" from the designated organisation.</li><li>meet the language requirements.</li><li>bring sufficient funds to settle. And applicant should also be able to financially support dependants.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<p>The applicant should provide the following documents:</p><ul><li>Identity documents</li><li>Proof of English language proficiency</li><li>Dependents documents, if applicable</li><li>Police certificate and clearance</li></ul>', '<p>Firstly, get the application package. After that, pay your application fees and submit your application.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">When to Apply</strong></p><p>Apply a year before you want to move to Canada.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Visa Processing Time</strong></p><p>It may take 12-16 months to process your application. There may be a need to provide biometrics along with your application. It includes the time which you need to give to your biometrics.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">How to Apply</strong></p><p>Gather your documents and apply online. You will have to provide biometrics for visa processing. However, you are advised to let the professionals handle the job for you.</p>', '<p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Duration</strong></p><p>You\'re normally allowed to stay in Canada indefinitely.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Fees</strong></p><p>The visa cost may vary by various factors. It starts from 2,075 CAD.</p><h3>How much money is required for a startup visa in Canada?</h3><p>200,000 CAD is the minimum amount you should secure for your business.&nbsp;</p>', '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(48, 48, 48);\">There is no need for an extension as this visa can lead to permanent residence in Canada.</span></p>', '<p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Business</strong></p><p>The visa is for investment and business in Canada.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Work</strong></p><p>You can apply for a temporary work permit.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Dependents</strong></p><p>Include family members on this visa.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Multi-entry</strong></p><p>Move-in and outside Canada as you want.</p>', NULL, 'pexels-n-voitkevich-72359111725772615985-9804.jpg', '[\"Business\",\"Extendable\",\"Dependants\",\"Citizenship\"]', 1, '2024-09-08 05:16:55', '2024-09-08 05:16:55', NULL),
(9, '2cd8d600-c8e1-458d-ae51-402672cafe3d', 'CA', '2 Years', 'Super Visa (for Parents & Grandparents) Canada', 'familyvisa', 1, 0, 1, 0, '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(48, 48, 48);\">Apply for a Super Visa if you wish to visit your kids or grandkids in Canada for two years. It is a multi-entry visa that allows multiple entries for ten years. You may also go with a six-month-long visitor visa. But the downside is if your visit exceeds six months, you will have to go through a visa extension process.</span></p>', '<p>To be eligible, you should:</p><ul><li>be a parent or a&nbsp;grandparent of a Canadian citizen or permanent resident.</li><li>have a letter signed by your child or grandchild inviting you to Canada.</li><li>get medical insurance from the insurance company in Canada.&nbsp;</li><li>be invited by a person who can support you financially.</li></ul><p><br></p>', '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(48, 48, 48);\">The immigration authorities may turn down a Super Visa application in the following circumstances: The Super Visa applicant\'s criminal record makes them inadmissible to Canada. Any facts concealed, misrepresented, or omitted entirely in the Super Visa application may result in rejection.</span></p>', '<p>Submit the following documents for Super Visa:</p><ul><li>Identity document</li><li>Proof of medical insurance with any&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.solutionsfinancial.ca/insurance-products/life-insurance-companies-in-canada/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 123, 255);\">Canadian Insurance company</a>.</li><li>A letter of invitation from the child or grandchild. These children must be Canadian citizens or permanent residents of Canada.</li><li>Proof that the sponsor can support you financially.</li></ul><p><br></p>', '<p>Applying online is the best option. It saves you from going through a courier service or visiting a visa office.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">When to Apply</strong></p><p>The visa may take up to a few weeks to process. You are advised to apply a month before moving to Canada as the time may differ for countries.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Visa Processing Time</strong></p><p>Processing times vary depending on the visa office. Most applications for a Super Visa are processed within a few weeks or less. The time also increases if some documents are missing. Moreover, you may also be asked for an interview or some extra information.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">How to Apply</strong></p><p>Although applying online is the best option, it can also be challenging. You may have to provide extra documents or take medical tests. To get through all that without much trouble, we advise you to let a visa consultant handle the job for you.</p>', '<p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Duration</strong></p><p>You can live in Canada for two years on a Super Visa. It also allows you to enjoy multi-entry for ten long years. The visa does not allow you to work in the country. That is why you may have to apply for a Work Permit in Canada.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Fees</strong></p><p>The visa cost starts from CAD 100. You also have to pay for a work or study permit to be involved in such activities.</p>', '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(48, 48, 48);\">This visa lets you stay in Canada for two years. If you want to stay any longer, you should apply for an extension. Apply for an extension a month before it expires.</span></p>', NULL, 'pexels-lara-jameson-88284001725772697516-7182.jpg', '[\"Family-Visit\",\"Extendable\"]', 1, '2024-09-08 05:18:17', '2024-09-08 05:18:17', NULL);
INSERT INTO `visa_and_immegration` (`id`, `uuid`, `country`, `duration`, `title`, `category`, `short_stay`, `business`, `family_visit`, `citizenship`, `about`, `eligibility`, `documents`, `process`, `duration_and_fees`, `extension`, `highlights`, `faq`, `bg_image`, `visa_options`, `is_public`, `createdAt`, `updatedAt`, `deletedAt`) VALUES
(10, '3f14bcbb-8bd9-4056-a42b-5a765a882859', 'SG', '1 - 3 Months', 'Short-Term Visit Pass Singapore', 'visitvisa', 1, 0, 1, 0, '<p>Although a Singapore tourist visa allows you to visit the country, you must first obtain a Singapore Short-Term Visit Pass before entering the country. It implies that the visa is only a pre-entry permit, not a Singapore entry guarantee.</p><p>The majority of visitors to Singapore do not require a visa. Countries requiring Singapore visas are classified as Assessment Level I or Assessment Level II. They can apply online using Singapore\'s e-Service.</p>', '<p>To be eligible, you must:</p><ul><li>be a tourist for medical purposes, or it should be a social visit.</li><li>hold a valid passport.</li></ul>', '<p>You need to provide the following documents for a Short-Term Visit Pass using the e-Service:</p><ul><li>Travel document (e.g., passport) with at least six months validity.</li><li>Disembarkation/Embarkation (D/E) number that can be found in your SG Arrival Card.</li><li>For foreigners with family ties whose immediate family members are Singapore Citizens or permanent residents, they require original supporting documents. These supporting documents must provide an evidence of your relationship with them.&nbsp;</li><li>Proof that you are financially stable enough for your stay.</li></ul><p><br></p>', '<p>You are allowed to travel to Singapore once your visa is processed. But you should know that while entering the country, the ICA (The Immigration and Checkpoints Authority) officers will decide if you\'re allowed to enter the country.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">When to Apply</strong></p><p>You should apply a week before you need it to be in the safe zone.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Visa Processing Time</strong></p><p>It takes atleast three working days to process this visa.&nbsp;</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">How to Apply</strong></p><p>All Short-Term Visit Pass applications must be submitted online using the e-Service. You may also consult a visa consultant in that matter.</p>', '<p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Duration</strong></p><p>The visa is for 30 days, and you should not stay any longer. But if you need to stay a bit longer, you can apply for a Short-Term Visit Pass extension of 90 days.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Fees</strong></p><p>The visa costs you 30 SGD. But if you want to extend it via a Short-Term Visit Pass extension, you may have to pay 40 SGD.</p>', '<p>An extension fee of 40 SGD is applicable when the current valid pass accumulates for 90 days or more from the pass\'s date of entry/issuance. This fee is chargeable for every subsequent extension of stay, accumulating to 90 days or more.</p><p>Foreigners widely use this extension in Singapore. Even if you are on a student pass and want to stay longer after it ends, you may apply for a Short-Term Visit Pass.</p><h3>Conditions for extending your Singapore Short-Term Visit Pass</h3><p>The following are the requirements for extending your Singapore Short-Term Pass:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>You need a local sponsor who is a minimum&nbsp;of 21 and has a SingPass account.&nbsp;</li><li>Before your current Short-Term Visit Pass expires, you must apply for it&nbsp;three working days in advance.&nbsp;</li><li>You do not plan to return to Singapore in the next five days after your visit ends.</li></ul>', '<p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Work</strong></p><p>You cannot work on this visa.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Travel</strong></p><p>The visa is for visit and tourism purposes. So, you can travel.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Citizenship</strong></p><p>Applicants cannot get citizenship through this visa.</p>', NULL, 'pexels-lara-jameson-88286151725773034671-1813.jpg', '[\"Tourism\",\"Extendable\",\"Short-Stay\"]', 1, '2024-09-08 05:23:54', '2024-09-08 05:23:54', NULL),
(11, 'f2f5f2ad-3008-45a7-98b5-619f0aeb3825', 'SG', '30+ Days', 'Student\'s Pass Singapore', 'studentvisa', 1, 0, 1, 0, '<p>A Student Visa is termed a Student\'s Pass in Singapore. A foreigner needs a \"Student\'s Pass\" who got accepted into a Singapore educational institution and has more than 30 days of academic program. Furthermore, their universities are referred to as&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nie.edu.sg/research/apply-for-grants/faqs-for-institutes-of-higher-learning\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 123, 255);\">Institutes of Higher Learning (IHL)</a>.&nbsp;</p><p>You do not need a Student\'s Pass if you have an Immigration Exemption Order. Or you have been granted a Short-Term Visit Pass at a Singapore Checkpoint and wish to attend a short course.</p><h3>Does Singapore reject Student Pass?</h3><p>There is no assurance that all Student Pass applications will be accepted. If you are denied this pass, you may want to consult a professional for&nbsp;advice.</p>', '<p>To be eligible, you:</p><ul><li>should be 19 years old and below at the time of application.</li><li>may have to go through an interview if you are older than 19.</li><li>invited by an institute in Singapore.</li></ul>', '<p>When called upon, applicants able to attend an interview need to submit&nbsp;the following documents:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Your original identification documents.</li><li>A Registration Acknowledgement Letter&nbsp;from that school which you have&nbsp;to attend.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Your private details, including a list of previous countries/locations where you have lived, your employment history, educational background, and financial support.&nbsp;</li><li>If applicable, personal information about your parents, spouse, and/or siblings.</li><li>In Singapore, your residential address and contact information.</li></ul>', '<p>You are not required to be in Singapore during the processing of your application. Therefore, apply for this Pass before arriving in Singapore. You will be unable to extend your stay while the application is still in process. If your application is approved, you can travel to Singapore to complete the necessary paperwork for your Student\'s Pass to be issued.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">When to Apply</strong></p><p>You must submit your application online using the e-Service at least four weeks before your course begins.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Visa Processing Time</strong></p><p>Processing time is from 2-4 months for cases requiring interviews. Inquiry on the outcome of the interview will not be entertained.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">How to Apply</strong></p><p>You\'ll need a local sponsor to apply for this Pass. The local sponsor must be at least 21 years old and a Permanent Resident (PR) or Singapore Citizen (SC).&nbsp;Companies and organisations are not permitted to serve as sponsors. If you have a PR or SC parent or step-parent, they can sponsor this Pass application locally.</p>', '<p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Duration</strong></p><p>The student pass is for students trying to apply for more than 30 days long course at a University in Singapore.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Fees</strong></p><p>The total cost is 90 SGD for a Student Pass. It includes 30 SGD for visa processing and 60 SGD for issuing a Student Pass. Fees are non-refundable.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Once their student pass has been cancelled or expired, graduates are usually issued a Short-Term Visit Pass by which they can stay in Singapore for 90 days. But if your program is still uncompleted, you may apply for a student visa renewal.</p>', '<p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Study</strong></p><p>The visa is only for study purposes.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Multi-entry</strong></p><p>You can enter and leave the country till your visa is valid.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Work</strong></p><p>Applicant cannot do any work.</p><p><strong style=\"color: gray;\">Citizenship</strong></p><p>You cannot apply for citizenship using this visa.</p>', NULL, 'pexels-lara-jameson-88283131725775369235-5219.jpg', '[\"Study\",\"Extendable\"]', 1, '2024-09-08 05:25:48', '2024-09-08 06:02:49', NULL),
(12, 'a48be2ee-e76f-4f19-9cb6-b858fb0c18df', 'AU', '1 3 months', 'asd', 'workvisa', 1, 0, 1, 0, '<p>asd</p>', '<p>asd</p>', '<p>fssdf</p>', '<p>sdf</p>', '<p>sdf</p>', '<p>sdf</p>', '<p>sdf</p>', '<p>sdf</p>', 'pexels-anthonybbeck-45140781725780446033-4939.jpg', '[\"Visitor\",\"Stay\"]', 1, '2024-09-08 07:27:26', '2024-09-08 07:27:26', NULL);

